      • context

        public android.content.Context context

      • sessionName

        Name for the session

      • deviceSsidRegex

        public java.lang.String deviceSsidRegex
        Regular expression string for SSID scans.

        This string is used to filter the list of SSIDs returned from a WiFi network scan. The default value returns SSIDs that begin with "Ayla", "T-Stat" or "Plug", followed by a dash and a string of 12 hexadecimal characters.

        If your device broadcasts a different SSID for WiFi setup, set this parameter to a regular expression that matches any supported devices' SSID.

      • appVersion

        public java.lang.String appVersion
        Application version. Passed to the Ayla library during initialization.

      • pushNotificationType

        public AylaServiceApp.PushType pushNotificationType
        Type of push notification supported by this application. One of AylaServiceApp.PushType.GooglePush or AylaServiceApp.PushType.BaiduPush

      • pushNotificationSenderId

        public java.lang.String pushNotificationSenderId
        Sender ID for push notifications. Android-specific. @see PushNotification for details.

      • appId

        public java.lang.String appId
        App ID passed to the Ayla library. Each app has its own unique ID.

      • appSecret

        public ViewModelProvider viewModelProvider
        ViewModelProvider object. Implementers should create a class derived from ViewModelProvider to return Device objects for this application. This object also implements the DeviceDetailProvider interface, which is required for SDK initialization.

      • enableLANMode

        public boolean enableLANMode
        Set to true to allow LAN mode operations application-wide. If this is set to true, the app will attempt to connect via the LAN to devices under certain circumstances. If set to false, LAN mode will not be attempted.

      • allowLANLogin

        public boolean allowLANLogin
        Set to true to allow the user to log in using cached credentials when the cloud service is not available, but the local network with devices on it is.

      • allowDSS

        public boolean allowDSS
        Set to true to allow the Device Subscription Service to keep devices up to date. This method will be used instead of polling device status by AylaDeviceManager. Set to false by default, as this is currently a beta feature.

      • ssoLogin

        public boolean ssoLogin
        Set to true to allow login to SSO Identity Provider service. false by default

      • dssSubscriptionTypes

        public java.lang.String[] dssSubscriptionTypes
        DSS subscription event types. Supported types are datapoint, datapointack, connectivity and location.

      • loggingLevel

        public AylaLog.LogLevel loggingLevel
        Logging level for console output from the Ayla library. Set to one of:
        • AylaLog.LogLevel#None
        • AylaLog.LogLevel#Error
        • AylaLog.LogLevel#Warning
        • AylaLog.LogLevel#Info
        • AylaLog.LogLevel#Verbose

      • deviceSortingDescriptors

        public java.lang.String[] deviceSortingDescriptors
        Specify a set of criteria by which the device list is sorted. One or more criteria can be specified. The device list will be sorted with the first criterion. Any subsequent criteria are used to further sort objects with same values of first criterion. Specifying deviceSortingDescriptors will override default deviceComparator. Valid sorting descriptors are dsn, connectedAt, productName, productClass, deviceName, and ssid

      • serviceLocation

        public AylaSystemSettings.ServiceLocation serviceLocation
        Service location: China, Europe, USA

      • serviceType

        public AylaSystemSettings.ServiceType serviceType
        Service to connect to. Generally during development, the Development service is used, while in production, Field service is used.
